WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:11.160
[Amit Varma]: For the last few years, our economy has been going down, down, down.

00:00:11.160 --> 00:00:13.880
[Amit Varma]: But our stock market has been going up, up, up.

00:00:13.880 --> 00:00:15.840
[Amit Varma]: Stock markets are a strange beast.

00:00:15.840 --> 00:00:21.020
[Amit Varma]: You can consider them to be the engine of a growing economy or a casino with no relation

00:00:21.020 --> 00:00:22.020
[Amit Varma]: to the real world.

00:00:22.020 --> 00:00:24.320
[Amit Varma]: For some, they are an object of loathing.

00:00:24.320 --> 00:00:26.880
[Amit Varma]: For others, they invoke hope and romance.

00:00:26.880 --> 00:00:32.160
[Amit Varma]: I just find them fascinating because they are both a picture of reality and a tussle

00:00:32.160 --> 00:00:34.920
[Amit Varma]: between the many fantasies in our heads.

00:00:34.920 --> 00:00:39.240
[Amit Varma]: In stock markets, the world of today collides with the world of tomorrow, and perception

00:00:39.240 --> 00:00:42.600
[Amit Varma]: matters as much as reality, at least in the short term.

00:00:42.600 --> 00:00:47.120
[Amit Varma]: I'm bullish on stock markets, though I'm not sure in a perfect world the stock markets

00:00:47.120 --> 00:01:04.360
[Unknown]: would be so bullish right now.

00:01:04.360 --> 00:01:05.360
[Amit Varma]: Welcome to The Scene and the Unseen.

00:01:05.360 --> 00:01:10.840
[Amit Varma]: My guest today is a brilliant Deepak Chinoy, an old friend known to the world as an investing

00:01:10.840 --> 00:01:15.960
[Amit Varma]: guru but known to me simply as one of the smartest and nicest and most interesting people

00:01:15.960 --> 00:01:16.960
[Amit Varma]: I know.

00:01:16.960 --> 00:01:22.160
[Amit Varma]: I never invited him onto the show ostensibly to talk about investing, but cunningly, my

00:01:22.160 --> 00:01:25.480
[Amit Varma]: intention was to pick his brains on much, much more.

00:01:25.480 --> 00:01:29.440
[Amit Varma]: The mental models through which he looks at the world, including markets, his insights

00:01:29.440 --> 00:01:35.320
[Amit Varma]: on investing, his insights on life, and hey, even for his bad jokes, which are second only

00:01:35.320 --> 00:01:36.320
[Amit Varma]: to mine.

00:01:36.320 --> 00:01:40.880
[Amit Varma]: Deepak runs Capital Mind, a Bangalore-based investment research and wealth management

00:01:40.880 --> 00:01:45.320
[Amit Varma]: startup and he also runs the Capital Mind podcast.

00:01:45.320 --> 00:01:47.720
[Amit Varma]: All those links will be in the show notes.

00:01:47.720 --> 00:01:54.800
[Amit Varma]: Before we get to our conversation, though, let's take a quick commercial break.

00:01:54.800 --> 00:01:59.900
[Amit Varma]: I often advise people not to invest in stock markets unless they have studied it first.

00:01:59.900 --> 00:02:01.860
[Amit Varma]: That old poker saying applies.

00:02:01.860 --> 00:02:04.400
[Amit Varma]: If you don't know who's the sucker at the table, it's you.

00:02:04.400 --> 00:02:08.120
[Amit Varma]: Well, if you do find it fascinating, then learn about it first.

00:02:08.120 --> 00:02:12.640
[Amit Varma]: Listening to this episode and picking up the books Deepak recommends is one way of doing

00:02:12.640 --> 00:02:13.640
[Amit Varma]: so.

